# Repository Pattern

Every feature owns a repository.

Repositories isolate data sources.

---

# Responsibilities

Repositories:

- combine local and remote data
- map DTOs
- expose domain models
- handle caching
- manage synchronization

Repositories never render UI.

---

# Structure

Feature

↓

Repository Interface

↓

Repository Implementation

↓

Datasource

---

# Data Sources

Separate:

RemoteDatasource

LocalDatasource

Never mix responsibilities.

---

# Domain Models

Repositories expose only domain models.

Never expose DTOs.

---

# Caching

Repositories determine:

cache

refresh

offline fallback

---

# Synchronization

When online:

refresh cache

When offline:

return cached data

---

# Multiple Sources

Repositories may combine:

API

Hive

Secure Storage

SQLite

Future providers

without exposing implementation.

---

# Naming

AuthenticationRepository

CourseRepository

QuizRepository

AIRepository

Avoid generic names.

---

# Testing

Mock repositories.

Never mock Dio in widget tests.

---

# Cursor Instructions

Generate:

interface

implementation

datasources

mapper

tests

Hide implementation details from presentation.